{"TopicId":166181,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Mars Colonization Discussion Thread","CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-10-05T14:52:03Z","PageNum":26,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Kerbal7","CreatedById":182165,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T00:34:54Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519259531\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154786\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheKSPBeginner\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 minute ago, TheKSPBeginner said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sorry, for WHAT!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds like the freaky city.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TheKSPBeginner","CreatedById":154786,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T00:35:35Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSounds more like a target for Kerbal armies to destroy.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Antstar","CreatedById":174784,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T04:24:56Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301002\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519236247\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182165\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal7\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Kerbal7 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEverything at Mars wants to kill you. Including the dirt.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ch1 style=\u0022background-color:#ffffff;color:#303030;font-size:28px;padding:0px;\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003EMars Surface Is Looking Much Deadlier Than We Previously Thought\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/h1\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.sciencealert.com/mars-surface-looks-to-be-much-more-deadly-than-we-previously-thought\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttps://www.sciencealert.com/mars-surface-looks-to-be-much-more-deadly-than-we-previously-thought\u003C/a\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI had not seen this. Thanks...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m a chemist. I promise you that 1) they are absolutely right: hard UV \u002B perchlorate is bad for organic chemistry, let alone life. 2) perchlorates are not toxic to humans in multi gram amounts. In fact they used to be available as lozenges. As the article implies, UV is the killer here. And the right plastic is like SPF 10000\u002B \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:P\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_tongue.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:P\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301093\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519243126\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: A series of satellites or landstrips does what exactly to create a planetary magnetic field ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut even a magnetic field would not enable Mars to hold an atmosphere (not enough gravity) and no speculative process can generate one faster than it escapes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I was going to propose the same thing. Rings around the planet, made of superconducting magnets. Outrageous, but not impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a CO2 atmosphere is a good start, at least you have pressure and rad protection. It is much easier to build a thick CO2 atmosphere. Just ask Venus \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T05:49:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301284\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519255912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022180784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022DAL59\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n6 hours ago, DAL59 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOnly one rotating city, for pregnancy.\u00A0\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe pregnancy would last for 18..21 years until the embryo can buy alcohol and marry by himself.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe body finishes growing at 20..25 age.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301337\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519259531\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022154786\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022TheKSPBeginner\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, TheKSPBeginner said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m sorry, for WHAT!?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nE.T. detected.\u003Cbr\u003E\nHumans do not put eggs outside, they incubate them right inside the body. Funny but true.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T08:30:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519273496\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022174784\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Antstar\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Antstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nActually I was going to propose the same thing. Rings around the planet, made of superconducting magnets. Outrageous, but not impossible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHere\u0027s the difference between our views. I think it \u003Cem\u003Eis\u003C/em\u003E impossible because nobody can move the mass and provide the energy, control the dynamics etc. pp. And i still don\u0027t see how that works.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe fantasies i read deal with how to heat the core in such way that it starts working as a dynamo. Like blow up the planet with a doomsday bomb, connect a giant battery and heat it by resistance (duracell might sponsor ;-)), coil up a wire around it and send a current through it to heat the core inductively ... this sort of things. All more or less funny and fantastic.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd it still won\u0027t help to hold a thick atmosphere.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Antstar said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd a CO2 atmosphere is a good start, at least you have pressure and rad protection. It is much easier to build a thick CO2 atmosphere. Just ask Venus \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is not enough atmosphere, Mars isn\u0027t Venus. Maybe one could persuade the bound O in the Marsian crust to come out (*), but C isn\u0027t really there in quantity. The atmosphere is extremely thin. And the O, once released, will immediately start live out its tendencies to oxidise the place again afap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n(*) timelines and energies needed are handwavingly ridiculous.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWell, be it as it may. Colonization will remain a fantasy for the next couple of decades and probably beyond. Meanwhile hopefully moar data comes in the picture gets moar complete than before ...\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Shpaget","CreatedById":45577,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T10:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223300577\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519194736\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182165\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Kerbal7\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/21/2018 at 7:32 AM, Kerbal7 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe will build a mirror \u003Cu\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003E300 miles\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/u\u003E across at Mars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s what, 0,25% of Mars cross section? Is that going to make a difference?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T11:42:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw we can turn Phobosian aluminium into magnetic rings, too. Let\u0027s vote.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T11:53:45Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, there is more than a minimum of aluminium in the Marsian crust, you don\u0027t need to throw down pebbles from Phobos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust bring this:\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AlbaGallery3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022315\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/AlbaGallery3.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022470\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand the mining stuff and all the industry and people you need to run it. And to use the raw materials it produces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAluminium anyone ? For a minimum price ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers with an aluminiumminimumimmunity :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: the water in the background is only the artist\u0027s impression\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-22T11:57:05Z\u0022 title=\u002202/22/2018 11:57  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 22, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Green Baron\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T14:06:53Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301648\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519300425\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOh, there is more than a minimum of aluminium in the Marsian crust, you don\u0027t need to throw down pebbles from Phobos.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nJust bring this:\u003Cimg alt=\u0022AlbaGallery3.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 height=\u0022315\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/AlbaGallery3.jpg\u0022 width=\u0022470\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nand the mining stuff and all the industry and people you need to run it. And to use the raw materials it produces.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAluminium anyone ? For a minimum price ?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCheers with an aluminiumminimumimmunity :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEdit: the water in the background is only the artist\u0027s impression\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably cheaper to extract it in space, what you call an aluminum drop on Mars . . . . . . .a bomb without an explosive charge. Good for dusting up those solar panels or occasionally upgrading the CEO who decided to settle on Mars.\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:cool:\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cool.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:cool:\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou could make them into aluminum parachutes, of course they would have to be resmelted on the ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T17:57:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/2NmCEim6rUo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-22T18:18:51Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301708\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519308413\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107380\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022PB666\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, PB666 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProbably cheaper to extract it in space, what you call an aluminum drop on Mars . . . . . . .a bomb without an explosive charge. Good for dusting up those solar panels or occasionally upgrading the CEO who decided to settle on Mars\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey can put solar panels on a mountain and drop metals to its foot. Then pull up with ropes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"PB666","CreatedById":107380,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T01:27:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519322239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/2NmCEim6rUo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nbefore the question mark as a comma and three more zeros.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut you know if you build you facilities underground in tunnels potentially you can take care of 3 of the major mars problems at once, shielding, deep enough and its not to difficult to hold atmosphere, and also you are able to move freely laterally to transport. The only thing is you need from the start to be very good at forging drilling equipment.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T04:45:01Z","Content":"\n\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\n2 100 000 000 000 USD = just 21 \u003Ca href=\u0022https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Indian_numbering_system\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ekharab\u003C/a\u003E USD\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli\u003E\n2 100 000 000 000 USD / ~10 000 ~= 210 000 000 BTC.\n\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cem\u003EBoring Company\u003C/em\u003E should found a Alaskan subsidiary: \u003Cem\u003ECool Mining Company\u003C/em\u003E.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt would mine bitcoins in a cool place and give money for Mars.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nP.S.\u003Cbr\u003E\nLater they can use the same equipment on Mars which is even cooler.\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis will make Martian colony economically self-sufficient.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-02-23T04:46:53Z\u0022 title=\u002202/23/2018 04:46  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EFebruary 23, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T06:06:19Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n$2.1 Trillion is a lot of \u0022flamethrower\u0022 gag gifts . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T06:23:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302423\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519365979\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002276097\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Diche Bach\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Diche Bach said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n$2.1 Trillion is a lot of \u0022flamethrower\u0022 gag gifts . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEasy, just sell a flamethrower to every other human on Earth.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T09:00:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw how should their flamethrowers work on Mars? There is no oxygen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither they are going to use some mixture which burns in CO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E, or they are preparing for tunnel battles. \u003Csub\u003EDoom, Minecraft, Dwarf Fortress\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T09:21:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302478\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519376422\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n21 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBtw how should their flamethrowers work on Mars? There is no oxygen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEither they are going to use some mixture which burns in CO\u003Csub\u003E2\u003C/sub\u003E, or they are preparing for tunnel battles. \u003Csub\u003EDoom, Minecraft, Dwarf Fortress\u003C/sub\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe flamethrowers would carry their own oxygen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyways, 2.1 trillion is way too low, considering its bassicly the same estimated cost of a Mars mission done by NASA, just to send 6\u00A0buddy\u0027s to Mars and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"YNM","CreatedById":98447,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T09:42:47Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301916\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519322239\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n15 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsEmbeddedVideo ipsEmbeddedVideo_limited\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022true\u0022 frameborder=\u00220\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 src=\u0022https://www.youtube.com/embed/2NmCEim6rUo?feature=oembed\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf things truly is perfect you won\u0027t need 1 million people to start though. Just \u003Ca href=\u0022https://goo.gl/maps/4bfWKhvuLcD2\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Estart with 30 racialy-diverse people\u003C/a\u003E, you get yourself a territory.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T14:01:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302484\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519377702\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe flamethrowers would carry their own oxygen.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyways, 2.1 trillion is way too low, considering its bassicly the same estimated cost of a Mars mission done by NASA, just to send 6\u00A0buddy\u0027s to Mars and back.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.1 trillion is too low for colonization, but a flags and footprints mission should only cost hundreds of billions, not trillions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wumpus","CreatedById":133850,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T14:20:49Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223301552\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519288219\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 2/22/2018 at 3:30 AM, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere is not enough atmosphere, Mars isn\u0027t Venus. Maybe one could persuade the bound O in the Marsian crust to come out (*), but C isn\u0027t really there in quantity. The atmosphere is extremely thin. And the O, once released, will immediately start live out its tendencies to oxidise the place again afap.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes Venus have a magnetosphere?\u00A0 While any colonization of Venus would be the last step in an excruciatingly long-term process (starting with teraforming), I\u0027m curious if it is indeed possible.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"NSEP","CreatedById":165635,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T15:09:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302588\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519394465\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n16 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2.1 trillion is too low for colonization, but a flags and footprints mission should only cost hundreds of billions, not trillions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn old article, but this is what i based it around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacenews.com/op-ed-mars-for-only-1-5-trillion/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://spacenews.com/op-ed-mars-for-only-1-5-trillion/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Green Baron","CreatedById":107381,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T15:21:18Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302600\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519395649\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022133850\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022wumpus\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, wumpus said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes Venus have a magnetosphere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. She rolls along slowly on her path ... not enough movement in the core :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bill Phil","CreatedById":127797,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T15:23:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302675\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519398545\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165635\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022NSEP\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n9 minutes ago, NSEP said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAn old article, but this is what i based it around.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca href=\u0022http://spacenews.com/op-ed-mars-for-only-1-5-trillion/\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Ehttp://spacenews.com/op-ed-mars-for-only-1-5-trillion/\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIn that article it gives a ballpark estimate of the first mission costing 230 billion. One mission. 230 billion. Not trillions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat 1.5 trillion estimate is for 9 missions, and it assumes that the vehicle is expended for each mission. Which is not likely. There are known methods to make reentry less demanding on the vehicle. A ballute system could do the job, making the transfer vehicle reusable and lowering the cost to less than a trillion for the program.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T15:46:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302689\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519399390\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022127797\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bill Phil\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n20 minutes ago, Bill Phil said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne mission. 230 billion. Not trillions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat 1.5 trillion estimate is for 9 missions\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThat\u0027s all right. Nine attempts. One successful. So, 1.5 trln per this.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Diche Bach","CreatedById":76097,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-02-23T15:47:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223302687\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022166181\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221519399278\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022107381\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Green Baron\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n19 minutes ago, Green Baron said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNope. She rolls along slowly on her path ... not enough movement in the core :-)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo foolin\u0027?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBit of a side-bar, but I\u0027m curious: why all the atmosphere? Like, super DENSE atmosphere, isn\u0027t it?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, it seems clear, only the \u0022cool kid\u0022 planets generate a magneto sphere . . .\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}